LineNo: 9460063,

Narrator: You dreamed about the future. You s...
en


You dreamed about the future. You saw a wealthier Sordland.\n\nThe country saw massive economic development over your next term. The remnants of the Soll era were long gone, businesses became more profitable and the markets were freed of regulation.\n\nAs the market became freer, the people of Sordland also became free. As the economic boom continued, the most critical problems vanished one by one. Sordland was finally letting go of its past.

LineNo: 9460187,

Narrator: You dreamed about the future. You s...
en


You dreamed about the future. You saw a Sordland of equality.\n\nThe country saw massive social and economic reforms over your next term. The remnants of the Soll era were long gone, the unequal wealth distribution was curbed, and the means of production were being transferred to the workers.\n\nSordland was finally letting go of its past. As the people became more equal, they also became free. Your social experiment was bringing Sordland one step closer to the revolution.

LineNo: 9460311,

Narrator: You dreamed about the future. You s...
en


You dreamed about the future. You saw a Sordland of security and stability.\n\nThe country saw massive social and economic development over your term. Your centrist approach helped the country heal and unite through a middle-ground.\n\nSordland was finally making peace with its past and learning to look to the future with hope. You brought harmony and confidence.

LineNo: 9460435,

Narrator: You dreamed about the future. You s...
en


You dreamed about the future. You saw a Sordland of self-reliant greatness.\n\nThe country saw massive social and economic reforms over your term. The state became stronger and provided the highest-quality services to its people with strides made towards autarky.\n\nSordland was finally embracing its true self. As the state became richer, the people earned comfort. You made Sordland even stronger than it was before.
